
	JENKINS
	
	jenkins is open source and it is entirely  written in JAVA
	jenkins is a CI/CD tool
	jenkins is a plugin based tool ,there are 1000+ plugin available in jenkins.
	jenkins also support cloud based architrcture so that you can deploy jenkins in cloud based platform.
	default port number is 8080
	
	
	and other CI tool 
	   jenkins 
	   bamboo
	   teamcity
	   
	   
	How many ways to install the jenkins:
	  1. by using yum command  or apt-get
	  2. deploying the jenkins in war file in tomcat
	  3. directly run the jenkins war file 
	  4. installation of jenkins using docker
	  
installation of jenkins in red hat centos fedora using yum command
   
    sudo amazon-linux-extras install java-openjdk11
	sudo amazon-linux-extras install epel
	curl --silent --location http://pkg.jenkins-ci.org/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo | sudo tee /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo
    rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io.key
    systemctl enable jenkins
	systemctl status jenkins.service
	systemctl start jenkins.service
	
	default path of jenkins is ===== var/lib/jenkins
